 the same single-variable marginals. We completely characterize this\npolytope, as well as the polytope of all possible probabilistic couplings for\ncyclic systems with given single-variable marginals.[...]\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 7 Jul 2019 18:19:32 GMT"},{"version":"v10","created":"Mon, 17 May 2021 20:22:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 1 Aug 2019 21:42:30 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 23 Sep 2019 17:11:19 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 4 Oct 2019 19:22:44 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Mon, 6 Jan 2020 12:56:46 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Tue, 3 Mar 2020 21:13:46 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Sat, 11 Apr 2020 01:22:54 GMT"},{"version":"v8","created":"Thu, 28 May 2020 13:06:13 GMT"},{"version":"v9","created":"Fri, 9 Apr 2021 16:19:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-05-19"}
